> We love a bit of fusion! So this Middle Eastern inspired chickpea salad with British runner beans is just a dream for us - good job André! Now, what's that extra magical sprinkle of flavour? It's Zahtar! It can be traced all the way back to biblical times - so it must be good if it's been popular for this long!

Pre-heat your oven to 200 degrees. Cut the @Ciabatta{1} in half lengthways and then cut each half into strips 2cm wide. Chop the strips into 2cm wide chunks, pop into a #bowl{} and add @Za'atar{1%tsp} and @olive oil{2%tbsp}. Toss well to make sure the zahtar spice mix is evenly distributed. Place on a #baking tray{} and bake for ~{8-10%mins}. When the croutons are golden and crunchy, remove from your oven and keep to one side. No snacking!

While your croutons bake, cut the @Red Onion{1} in half, peel and slice into thin half moon shapes. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}.

Chop the tops and bottoms off the @Runner Beans{1} and cut each bean into 3cm sized pieces.

Roughly chop the @Flat Leaf Parsley{1}, strip the @Oregano{1} leaves off their stalks and zest the @Lemon{1}.

Bring a #pot{} of water to the boil on high heat. When the water is boiling, add @salt{1/4%tsp} and cook the runner beans for ~{4%mins}. Drain in a #colander{} and keep to one side.

As the beans cook, heat a #saucepan{} on medium heat and add @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Cook the red onion for ~{3%mins} with @salt{1/4%tsp}. When the onion has softened, add the grated garlic and @Red Wine Vinegar{1}. Cook for ~{2%mins} or until the vinegar has evaporated.

Drain the @Chickpeas{1} and rinse under cold water. Add the chickpeas to the pan and warm through. Toss in the runner beans and warm them through too.

Remove the pan from the heat and add your parsley and oregano. Squeeze in half your lemon juice. Add your zest and the remaining @Za'atar{1%tsp}. Check the seasoning and add another pinch of @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{pinch} along with another squeeze of lemon if you feel it needs it.

Cut the @Feta Cheese{1} into 2cm cubes and get ready to serve.

Spoon a generous amount of your bean salad into a #deep bowl{} and scatter over some croutons. Finish with your cubes of feta cheese and a drizzle of your best @olive oil{}. Delicious!